review_blob: Pours amber brown with tan head. Aroma is overwhelming dark figgy fruits. Flavor is light and fruity with not as much malt body as one might expect. The high level of carbonation seems to cut the the palate short but then lasting caramel lingers. Very good Marzen.

Pours a dark clear chestnut color with ample off-white head. Aroma wants to be nutty but the hop hash is too overpowering. To taste though, the smoked malts shine and work well with the bitter hops. The bitterness lingers and there is a very nice smoky flavor to the finish that adds something extra and leaves the palate ultimately satisfied

Pours clear amber (not remotely "white") with light tan head. Aroma is very floral and sweet with a pinch of piney spruce. The beer is very carbonated and the flavor feels very muted. Pours clear straw colored with plentiful foamy white head. Aroma is very standard for the style with slightly tart doughy yeast esters. Flavor is somewhat unique with light banana notes dominating most of the flavor. The yeast flavors are still left on the palate however, once all is said and done.
